The new features of the program compared with Roosevelt's New Deal are:

① Attach importance to the development of education and science and technology;
② Increase government intervention in the economy;
③ Pay attention to environmental protection and energy saving;
④ Increase the government's public investment to create job opportunities.

The new features of the program are focused on education and science and technology, increasing government intervention in the economy, paying attention to environmental protection and energy saving, and increasing the government's public investment to create job opportunities. These are not features of Roosevelt's New Deal.
